# shellcheck configuration for traffic-generator
# This repo contains attack simulation scripts with intentional patterns
# that trigger false positives.

# Disable SC2016: Expressions don't expand in single quotes.
# All single-quoted $var references in this repo are intentional jq variables,
# not missed shell expansions.
disable=SC2016

# Disable SC2034: Variable appears unused.
# Attack scripts set variables for use in sourced library scripts (_lib.sh,
# _crapi-lib.sh, etc.) and trap handlers.
disable=SC2034

# Disable SC1091: Not following sourced file.
# Scripts source _lib.sh, _crapi-lib.sh, etc. via relative paths.
disable=SC1091

# Disable SC2064: Use single quotes for trap to prevent early expansion.
# Attack scripts intentionally expand variables at trap-set time.
disable=SC2064

# Disable SC2045: Iterating over ls output is fragile.
# Runner scripts iterate over numbered test scripts in controlled directories.
disable=SC2045

# Disable SC2002: Useless cat.
disable=SC2002

# Disable SC2106: This only exits the subshell.
disable=SC2106

# Disable SC2012: Use find instead of ls.
# Scripts use ls -d to count kernel queue directories.
disable=SC2012

# Disable SC2086: Double quote to prevent globbing and word splitting.
# PID lists and attack payloads intentionally rely on word splitting.
disable=SC2086

# Disable SC2030: Modification of variable is local to subshell.
# Parallel execution uses backgrounded subshells by design.
disable=SC2030

# Disable SC2031: Variable was modified in a subshell.
disable=SC2031

# Disable SC2001: See if you can use ${variable//search/replace}.
# Attack scripts use sed for complex regex patterns.
disable=SC2001

# Disable SC2155: Declare and assign separately.
# Attack scripts use compact local+assign for readability.
disable=SC2155

# Disable SC2000: See if you can use ${#variable} instead.
# Scripts use echo | wc -c for byte counting in pipeline context.
disable=SC2000
